name: Hoffman's Chocolate

name: SC4 College Center (Library/Cafe)

name: The Rendezvous
directions: 2 single-occupant unisex bathrooms at rear of restaurant. One is visible at rear left corner, the other is down a hallway at the rear right.

name: Target
directions: Towards the front of the store

name: William Paterson University

name: Red White & Que Smokehouse

name: McMaster University Medical Centre
directions: 4th floor beside pain clinic (near yellow elevator)

name: Pens & Needles Custom Tattoos
street: 716 N Weber St, Colorado Springs, CO 80903

name: Multi-purpose office building
directions: The restroom on the THIRD floor is gender neutral (a signal / family style restroom).
comment: Doesn't belong to any particular business in the shared building. I'm not sure on accessibility but there is at least an elevator. The restrooms on the FIRST floor are sex-segregated and multi-stall. I don't know about the basement or second floor.

name: The Loft
directions: Single stall genderless restroom around the corner to the left on the first floor. Not sure about accessibility.

name: Famous Faces and Funnies
directions: It's located in a hallway between the big open front room and the back room. The store is two big rooms, connected by the hallway so it isn't hard to find.
comment: The bathroom is one room- there's no stall, just a toilet and sink. It's a large room, and the toilet is low and has handrails, so it's a little more accessible as well. The staff doesn't care if you use the restroom, just go on in and use it. The hallway offers a little privacy too- it's not right  by the register so you don't have to feel shy going in or out.

name: Caf√© Rome
directions: Near the middle of the cafe, on the right side.
comment: It'll be hard to use the restroom without being a paying customer. I don't know if they'll stop you from using it, but it's right across from the cashier, so you can't exactly sneak in just to use it.

name: Target
directions: In the front, to the left of the front doors when you just walk in. Kind of almost hidden in the back by guest services. (Before you get to the gendered restrooms.)

name: Jamba Juice
comment: Don't remember if it's accessible or not... but you shouldn't have to be a paying customer to use it, I don't think.

name: Caf√© Cralle
directions: if you enter the caf√© there ist first the main and smoking room, you go through that and the second room. its at the end of the caf√©.
comment: There is a no CIS-Men allowed toilette and a 2. all genders toilette. its a feminist women collectiv caf√©.

name: JuiceLand
directions: first floor, near kitchen

name: Walmart
directions: In the back of Walmart right next to the second set of bathrooms. It's a family bathroom

name: Starbucks
comment: 2 gender neutral single stall

name: Blue Plate Diner
comment: Paying Customer

name: Cook's Corner
directions: Clearly marked toward back of diner
comment: Suggested that you are a paying customer, but not required. Prices are reasonable and food is excellent so worth it regardless

name: Starbucks
comment: Requires a code from the employees, no purchase necessary.

name: RAYMI Restaurant
directions: 1 gender neutral wheelchair accessible bathroom upstairs. 10 individual gender neutral single stalls downstairs.
comment: Upstairs and downstairs restrooms only available to restaurant patrons. Single stall downstairs bathrooms only open for dinner service starting at 5pm

name: Downers Grove public library
directions: Single gendered stall located in the children's area, by the printer. Head left from the circulation desk.

name: Aberystwyth Students' Union
directions: Up stairs, but I think outside there is a ramp. Go through the main bar and both toilets are gender neutral now though one has urinals.

name: Fenton Hall
directions: second floor, straight across from the main (east) entrance, past the main mathematics office and down a short hallway - two all-gender washrooms with locking doors.  The main entrance has stairs; the accessible entrance is on the south side of the building, then take the elevator to the second floor.  The first-floor washrooms are gendered, if I recall, but they are private and have locking doors. There may also be all-gender restrooms on the third floor, I forget.

name: Pinion ridge rest area
directions: Directly across from entrance

name: Target
directions: Inside the doors, just to the right

name: Knarvik Senter
comment: There's one door which leads to an accessible gender neutral bathroom with a baby changing station, and one door which leads to a non-accessible gender neutral bathroom with two stalls

name: Best Bagels in Town
comment: Paying customers only, staff-enforced.

name: Manna Grocery and Deli
directions: Down the hallway in the back right of the building
comment: Friendly staff

name: Stuhr Museum
directions: Second floor of the Stuhr Building.
comment: You have to pay museum admission to use this restroom.

name: Nike Running Flatiron, Retail
directions:
You can use the elevator or the stairs, it's on the bottom floor/"womens floor"
You require a code to enter, all the employees know it and will let you in if you ask for the bathroom. because of the size of the place it is technically a public bathroom and we always let people use it. Bathrooms are gendered but single stall each and no one ever cares who uses which.
comment:
You do not have to be paying customer just act casual if you can and ask to use the bathroom.
Someone will let you in and that's it. I'm not sure if the building is 100% accessible, but there is an elevator and a side door on 5th so you don't have to use the steps. The music can get pretty load sometimes and people may talk to you a lot to offer help just as a warning.

name: Walmart
directions: in the back, near the photo lab
comment: also has multi-stall restrooms near the service desk in the front, these are NOT recommended

name: Apple
directions: At the back of the store on the left. Through the door under the exit sign. Two separate single stall unisex restrooms.

name: The Crepe Vine
directions: down the stairs at the back then on the far right
comment: pretty sure you have to be a "paying customer" but its often busy and you can pretend you're meeting someone in the back then go down the stairs

name: University of Dundee Library
directions: SIngle stalls in group study areas on each floor
comment: Need to have a student card to enter building

name: Relish Gourmet Burgers
directions: Towards the back of the restaurant
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer, any one can use these washrooms

name: Starbucks VCC
directions: Slight left when walking in.

name: Target
directions: Front of store, next to photo area and check out lanes.
comment: Marked 'Family Restroom'. Free for anyone to use.

name: Funagain Games
directions: All the way in the back
comment: No requirement just browsing through

name: Plaza Inn and Suites
directions: Down the hall on the right, past the front desk
comment: Say you are with a guest

name: Little Caesars
directions: The door to the left of the lobby, single toilet closed room with lock. We're very friendly here! (2 trans workers actually)

name: Self Serve
comment: single occupancy room.

name: Sidewinders Bar
comment: one room is labelled "butch" and the other "fabulous". you can use whichever fits that day or just whichever one is closer. nobody will look twice no matter which one you use.

name: Maryville College Thaw Library
directions: Located beside the bottom of the left staircase in the entryway.
comment: Maryville College has safe places in nearly every building with stickers marking the doors.

name: Apple Store, The Promenade at Chenal
directions: Back of store, Behind green Exit sign
comment: No need to be paying or browsing customer - one marked symbol "female" stall and another separate marked symbol "male" stall only because of law - both open to anyone. Many trans and allied persons on staff ready to assist any conflicts - if in need just ask!

name: Wild Cow Vegetarian Restaraunt
directions: In the back to the right.
comment: Very lgbt friendly business.

name: Gordon Praus Frozen Yogurt
directions: Through the door in the back of the store
comment: They probably prefer paying customers but i've used it without buying anything. Store is open late, often until 9-10pm.

name: Gordon Praus Frozen Yogurt
directions: Through the door in the back of the store
comment: They probably prefer paying customers but i've used it without buying anything. Store is open late, often until 9-10pm.

name: new york bagel company
directions: straight down the hall beyond the dining area
comment: the place is not very busy except around lunchtime and the restrooms are gendered single-stall restrooms. no one will ask questions if you're just in there to go to the restroom.

name: Ku-Ring-Gai Wildflower Garden
directions: near the senses trail, to the left at the first turn off when you enter the park. (there are several more further into the park)
comment: 2 large single stalls near each other, technically gendered but nobody around really cares

name: Gwar Bar
directions: The left hand restroom has a toilet and urinal but both restrooms are unisex.

name: Cobb Lakeside 18 & IMAX
directions: After entering from front of theatre, labeled as "Family Restroom" in the right wing of the building. Will be to the left of the women's restroom.
comment: Don't need to pay for a ticket or concessions to use, just make sure to let the employee on tickets know.

name: Wal-Mart
directions: Back of store by photo center
comment: Restroom is very clean but the sink is tempermentle. If you drive truck this place is very friendly and easy to get into.

name: Target (Peoria Crossings)
directions: Next to the pharmacy, on the south wall of the store (front)
comment: Target has an open policy when it comes to bathrooms but your safety and comfort is important. It is a single stall, it doesn't require a key and purchase isn't necessary. There is a baby changing table. I believe it may be marked as a family restroom.

name: Reid Park Zoo
directions: directly to the right as you walk in the entrance
comment: have to pay to get in, although knowing the staff it wouldnt hurt to ask to use the bathroom.

name: Guiseppe's Cucina Rustica
directions: There are two gendered single room restrooms in the first dining room, but you can walk back through the patio to the back dining area where there are two more single gender private bathrooms and one unisex private bathroom
comment: Probably have to be a paying customer but you can buy something small at the express/deli counter

name: Forsyth Hall - Northeastern University
directions: Second floor. Private, non-gendered single bathroom.

name: luckys last chance
directions: just past the bar
comment: tell a bar tender you need a safe restroom to use

name: Riverdale Super A foods
street: Not sure of street address, sorry
directions: Get a key from the gasbar, restrooms are label A and B

name: Starbucks
directions: Shares a parking lot with Macy's. Restrooms are on your right when you walk in.
comment: I don't know if you have to be a customer, but the staff seem laid back. Doors lock behind you.

name: Roscoe's Coffee Bar and Tap Room
directions: Head on back down past the counters and it'll be to your right once you're in the room with the couches and tables. It's a small place so the bathrooms are hard to miss!
comment: Free to use at any time, sometimes people just go there to hang out and it's not required you buy anything. If you feel anxious about not looking like a customer, you can get a free water at the counter.

name: McKay Hall
directions: In McKay Hall (dormitory attached to Iggy's Diner). 1st floor. Next to the common room + kitchen.
comment: Need card access to enter McKay Hall. If you wait around outside, though, a student will probably come by and let you in.

name: South Towne Center
directions: The bottom floor outside of Forever 21 has a single stall family restroom with a locking door. Down a long hallway halfway between Forever 21 and the fountain.

name: Jumping Bean
directions: In between the seating area and counter

name: Silver Cinemas
directions: Near Dillard's and DSW
comment: Do not need to be a paying customer

name: Cafe Patachou
directions: Head back past the coffee bar. It's across from the kitchen.

name: Smith's Marketplace
directions: When entering the store, turn left and just continue straight towards the pharmacy. The bathrooms are once again on the left. There are two stalls, both unisex, and they lock. Handicap accessible (I believe--I'm abled so I don't know for sure).
comment: No idea if you must be a paying customer or not. To be safe, browse a bit.

name: CNM West Side Campus
directions: WSI building, ground floor in the outside courtyard

name: Starbucks
comment: " Paying customers only "

name: Edgewood High School
directions: Turn left after the vending machine area/in front of the gym in the main commons. Bathroom will be just a couple doors down to the right in this hallway.
comment: Have to be student/staff of school or attending school event to use.

name: City Hall
directions: On ground floor, down hallway past elevator.

name: Mashiko
directions: in the back behind the sushi bar
comment: you have to be a paying customer

name: Walmart West

name: Lisa's Legit Burrito's

name: Capitol Computers

name: Elements Books Coffee Beer
comment: Paying customers

name: La Crepe du Jour

comment: You do not have to purchase anything in order to use the bathroom. Be warned that it is very small, though.

name: McArthur Public Library

name: Texas Roadhouse
directions: All the way in the back left corner from the entrance

name: Crooked Tree Coffeehouse
directions: Far back right of dining room

name: Point Park University- Academic Hall
directions: First floor, across from the elevators (behind glass wall)
comment: Need Point Park ID to get into building, but good for students/educators!

name: Bulmer Telecommunications Center
directions: By the entrance closest to the administration building and the photo studio/room 1112
comment: You have to be a student at HVCC; There are 2 bathrooms, the one on the right has a drafty window so I'd recommend using the one to the left if you can

name: Ajax Public Library
directions: Second floor; go up the stairs and there's two unisex washrooms on your left around the corner

name: Kohls
directions: Back of the store, Family restroom with adult toilet, changing stall, and toddler-sized toilet in bathroom large enough to fit a wheelchair
